title: Looking Like a Title Defender, Georgia Thrashes Oregon
description: Before cruising, the Bulldogs built a 28-3 lead at halftime over the 11th-ranked Ducks. And Oregon didn’t score again. Yeah, it was that ugly.
dc:creator: Alan Blinder
media:credit: John David Mercer/USA Today Sports, via Reuters
media:description: Georgia’s Malaki Starks intercepted a throw from Oregon’s Bo Nix in the first half. Things went downhill for Oregon from there.
